      <memberdef kind="function" id="lookupVolumeFromMesh_8h_1a4ffd9679b27154a9a0b613f14f06c55f" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>double</type>
        <definition>double convertConcToNumRateInTwoCompts</definition>
        <argsstring>(double v1, unsigned int n1, double v2, unsigned int n2, double scale)</argsstring>
        <name>convertConcToNumRateInTwoCompts</name>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>v1</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>unsigned int</type>
          <declname>n1</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>v2</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>unsigned int</type>
          <declname>n2</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>double</type>
          <declname>scale</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Generates conversion factor for rates from concentration to mol# units. This variant is used when the reactants are in different compartments or mesh entries, and may therefore have different volumes. We already know the reactants and their affiliations. We use the first vol, v1, as the reference. The outcome of this calculation is: kf = Kf * convertConcToNumRate. The scale term is a conversion from the conc units to SI: The scale term is 1 if conc units are in SI, which is equal to moles per cubic metre, which is equal to millimolar. The scale term is 1e-3 for micromolar, uM.</para>
<para>Generates conversion factor for rates from concentration to mol# units. This variant is used when the reactants are in different compartments or mesh entries, and may therefore have different volumes. We already know the reactants and their affiliations. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
